## Agent 10 — Assembler (run LAST)

```
You are assembling the final hero.html file from 9 fragments produced by other agents.

1. Read ./HERO_BUILD_PLAN.md — focus on CARD 0 and CARD 10.
2. Read all 9 fragments at ./parts/card_1.html through ./parts/card_9.html.
3. Produce ./hero.html as a single valid HTML5 document:
   - <head> includes <meta charset>, viewport meta, Google Fonts <link> for Inter, and a single consolidated <style> block.
   - The <style> block starts with the CARD 0 :root variables, then concatenates every fragment's CSS (deduplicate any rules that appear identically across fragments).
   - <body> contains one <section class="hero"> built per CARD 10's semantic structure, pasting each fragment's markup in the correct slot.
   - Replace the <!-- BRAND_MARK_SLOT --> placeholder in card_2 with the brand-mark markup from card_3.
4. Apply the layout rules from CARD 10: .hero positioning, .hero-content flex stack, vertical rhythm gaps, z-index map.
5. Add the <body> base reset: margin: 0, font-family from CARD 0, antialiasing.
6. Open the file mentally and walk through every acceptance criterion from every card you can verify by reading the markup. Fix anything broken before finishing.
7. Add a <!-- TODO: mobile nav --> comment where CARD 10 mentions the hamburger.

Final deliverable: ./hero.html — a single self-contained file that opens correctly in a browser.
```

